Eight Wonders of Everyday Life (Sources of Awe): Based on stories gathered from 26 countries, the most common sources of awe are:
Nature
Spiritual Experience
Visual Art
Music
Big Ideas (epiphanies, profound concepts like dark matter)
Collective Movement (sporting events, dance)
Life and Death (the life cycle)
Moral Beauty (the most common worldwide source, encompassing acts of sacrifice, courage, overcoming adversity, and justice/speaking truth to power).













